snippet: Rescuers trying to shepherd surviving short-finned pilot whales out to open sea were stymied by sharks that had feasted on the carcasses.
abstract: Rescuers in southwest Florida are attempting to guide pod of stranded pilot whales back to their home range at sea, but efforts are being stymied by sharks feasting on those whales that had already died; some whales have successful returned offshore, but death count also continues to rise.
lead_paragraph: Rescuers trying to shepherd surviving short-finned pilot whales out to open sea were stymied by sharks that had feasted on the carcasses.

headline.main: Stranded Pilot Whales Die in Florida Everglades
headline.print_headline: Stranded Pilot Whales Die in Florida Everglades as Rescuers Try to Save Podmates
